        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Dear Mr Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>O that I had the<lb/> arms of &#91;&#63;&#93; with hands<lb/> to each&#44; all able to write&#45;&#45;<lb/> But I have not.&#45;&#45; Things are<lb/> going satisfactory. I sent out<lb/> only about 150 to 160 circulars to a few<lb/> odd names to obtain  their signatures<lb/> to append to the circular when we<lb/> scatter it broadcast so as to give<lb/> it weight. Of course some have<lb/> replied&#34;some have not. But<lb/> a very pleasant and encouraging<lb/> <hi rend="underline">feature</hi> is that some have not only<lb/>signed their names but have<lb/> become subscribers patrons or<lb/> Donors&#34;one sent check &#36;15 donation besides<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Another  becomes annual subscriber of &#36;25<lb/> and gives besides &#36;100.&#45;&#45; and in as<lb/> much as they are people whom<lb/> we would hardly think could countenance<lb/> us&#44; I think a liberal scattering of the<lb/> circulars would produce good affect&#45;&#45;<lb/></p> 
            <p>I enclose Dr S&#39;s letter&#91;.&#93; please <lb/>return it&#45;&#45; I send herewith<lb/> your copy of Constitution&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>In &#91;&#63;&#93; haste<lb/>
                Yrs H Pereira Mendes&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/></p>
                
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Rev. Dr. H. Pereira Mendes.<lb/>
                318 West 30<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Street.<lb/>
                New York.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S Morias<lb/>
                546 N 5<lb/>
                Philad<lb/>
                Pa<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
